 0223:     """
 0224:     Susceptible, Infected, Removed (SIR)
 0225:     Ia: asymptomatic
 0226:     Is: symptomatic
 0227:     
 0228:     Latent inference class to be used when observed data is incomplete.
 0229:     ...
 0230: 
 0231:     Parameters
 0232:     ----------
 0233:     parameters: dict
 0234:         Contains the following keys:
 0235:             alpha: float
 0236:                 Estimate mean value of fraction of infected who are asymptomatic.
 0237:             beta: float
 0238:                 Estimate mean value of rate of spread of infection.
 0239:             gIa: float
 0240:                 Estimate mean value of rate of removal from asymptomatic individuals.
 0241:             gIs: float
 0242:                 Estimate mean value of rate of removal from symptomatic individuals.
 0243:             fsa: float
 0244:                 fraction by which symptomatic individuals self isolate.
 0245:             cov: np.array( )
 0246:                 Covariance matrix for all the estimated parameters.
 0247:             S0: np.array(M,)
 0248:                 Estimate initial number of susceptables.
 0249:             Ia0: np.array(M,)
 0250:                 Estimate initial number of asymptomatic infectives.
 0251:             Is0: np.array(M,)
 0252:                 Estimate initial number of symptomatic infectives.
 0253:             cov_init : np.array((3*M, 3*M)) :
 0254:                 Covariance matrix for the initial state.
 0255:                 
 0256:     M: int
 0257:         Number of compartments of individual for each class.
 0258:         I.e len(contactMatrix)
 0259:     Ni: np.array(3*M, )

 0651:     """
 0652:     Susceptible, Exposed, Infected, Removed (SEIR)
 0653:     Ia: asymptomatic
 0654:     Is: symptomatic
 0655:     
 0656:     Latent inference class to be used when observed data is incomplete.
 0657:     
 0658:     Parameters
 0659:     ----------
 0660:     parameters: dict
 0661:         Contains the following keys:
 0662:             alpha: float
 0663:                 Estimate mean value of fraction of infected who are asymptomatic.
 0664:             beta: float
 0665:                 Estimate mean value of rate of spread of infection.
 0666:             gIa: float
 0667:                 Estimate mean value of rate of removal from asymptomatic individuals.
 0668:             gIs: float
 0669:                 Estimate mean value of rate of removal from symptomatic individuals.
 0670:             fsa: float
 0671:                 fraction by which symptomatic individuals self isolate.
 0672:             gE: float
 0673:                 Estimated mean value of rate of removal from exposed individuals.
 0674:             cov: np.array( )
 0675:                 covariance matrix for all the estimated parameters.
 0676:             S0: np.array(M,)
 0677:                 Estimate initial number of susceptables.
 0678:             E0: np.array(M,)
 0679:                 Estimate initial number of exposed.
 0680:             Ia0: np.array(M,)
 0681:                 Estimate initial number of asymptomatic infectives.
 0682:             Is0: np.array(M,)
 0683:                 Estimate initial number of symptomatic infectives.
 0684:             cov_init : np.array((3*M, 3*M)) :
 0685:                 Covariance matrix for the initial state.
 0686:     M: int
 0687:         Number of compartments of individual for each class.
 0688:         I.e len(contactMatrix)
 0689:     Ni: np.array(4*M, )
 0690:         Initial number in each compartment and class
 0691: 
 0692:     Methods
 0693:     -------
 0694:     simulate

 0883:     """
 0884:     Susceptible, Exposed, Infected, Removed (SEIR)
 0885:     Ia: asymptomatic
 0886:     Is: symptomatic

 0888:     Parameters
 0889:     ----------
 0890:     parameters: dict
 0891:         Contains the following keys:
 0892:             alpha: float
 0893:                 Estimate mean value of fraction of infected who are asymptomatic.
 0894:             beta: float
 0895:                 Estimate mean value of rate of spread of infection.
 0896:             gIa: float
 0897:                 Estimate mean value of rate of removal from asymptomatic individuals.
 0898:             gIs: float
 0899:                 Estimate mean value of rate of removal from symptomatic individuals.
 0900:             fsa: float
 0901:                 fraction by which symptomatic individuals self isolate.
 0902:             gE: float
 0903:                 Estimated mean value of rate of removal from exposed individuals.
 0904:             gA: float
 0905:                 Estimated mean value of rate of removal from activated individuals.
 0906:             cov: np.array( )
 0907:                 covariance matrix for all the estimated parameters.
 0908:             tE  : float
 0909:                 testing rate and contact tracing of exposeds
 0910:             tA  : float
 0911:                 testing rate and contact tracing of activateds
 0912:             tIa: float
 0913:                 testing rate and contact tracing of asymptomatics
 0914:             tIs: float

 1123:     """
 1124:     Susceptible, Exposed, Infected, Removed (SEIR)
 1125:     Ia: asymptomatic
 1126:     Is: symptomatic
 1127:     A: Asymptomatic and infectious 
 1128:     
 1129:     Latent inference class to be used when observed data is incomplete.
 1130:     Parameters
 1131:     ----------
 1132:     parameters: dict
 1133:         Contains the following keys:
 1134:             alpha: float
 1135:                 Estimate mean value of fraction of infected who are asymptomatic.
 1136:             beta: float
 1137:                 Estimate mean value of rate of spread of infection.
 1138:             gIa: float
 1139:                 Estimate mean value of rate of removal from asymptomatic individuals.
 1140:             gIs: float
 1141:                 Estimate mean value of rate of removal from symptomatic individuals.
 1142:             fsa: float
 1143:                 fraction by which symptomatic individuals self isolate.
 1144:             gE: float
 1145:                 Estimated mean value of rate of removal from exposed individuals.
 1146:             gA: float
 1147:                 Estimated mean value of rate of removal from activated individuals.
 1148:             cov: np.array( )
 1149:                 covariance matrix for all the estimated parameters.
 1150:             tE  : float
 1151:                 testing rate and contact tracing of exposeds
 1152:             tA  : float
 1153:                 testing rate and contact tracing of activateds
 1154:             tIa: float
 1155:                 testing rate and contact tracing of asymptomatics
 1156:             tIs: float
 1157:                 testing rate and contact tracing of symptomatics
 1158:             S0: np.array(M,)
 1159:                 Estimate initial number of susceptables.
 1160:             E0: np.array(M,)
 1161:                 Estimate initial number of exposed.
 1162:             A0: np.array(M,)
 1163:                 Estimate initial number of activated.
 1164:             Ia0: np.array(M,)
 1165:                 Estimate initial number of asymptomatic infectives.
 1166:             Is0: np.array(M,)
 1167:                 Estimate initial number of symptomatic infectives.
 1168:             Q0: np.array(M,)
 1169:                 Estimate initial number of quarantined.
 1170:             cov_init : np.array((3*M, 3*M)) :
 1171:                 Covariance matrix for the initial state.
 1172:     M: int
 1173:         Number of compartments of individual for each class.
 1174:         I.e len(contactMatrix)
 1175:     Ni: np.array(4*M, )
 1176:         Initial number in each compartment and class

 1389:     """
 1390:     Susceptible, Exposed, Activates, Infected, Removed (SEAIR)
 1391:     The infected class has 5 groups:
 1392:     * Ia: asymptomatic
 1393:     * Is: symptomatic
 1394:     * Ih: hospitalized
 1395:     * Ic: ICU
 1396:     * Im: Mortality
 1397: 
 1398:     S  ---> E
 1399:     E  ---> Ia, Is
 1400:     Ia ---> R
 1401:     Is ---> Ih, R
 1402:     Ih ---> Ic, R
 1403:     Ic ---> Im, R
 1404:     Parameters
 1405:     ----------
 1406:     parameters: dict
 1407:         Contains the following keys:
 1408:             alpha: float
 1409:                 Estimate mean value of fraction of infected who are asymptomatic.
 1410:             beta: float
 1411:                 Estimate mean value of rate of spread of infection.
 1412:             gIa: float
 1413:                 Estimate mean value of rate of removal from asymptomatic individuals.
 1414:             gIs: float
 1415:                 Estimate mean value of rate of removal from symptomatic individuals.
 1416:             fsa: float
 1417:                 fraction by which symptomatic individuals self isolate.
 1418:             gE: float
 1419:                 Estimate mean value of rate of removal from exposeds individuals.
 1420:             gA: float
 1421:                 Estimate mean value of rate of removal from activated individuals.
 1422:             gIh: float
 1423:                 Rate of hospitalisation of infected individuals.
 1424:             gIc: float
 1425:                 Rate hospitalised individuals are moved to intensive care.
 1426:             cov: np.array
 1427:                 covariance matrix for all the estimated parameters.
 1428:             sa: float, np.array (M,)
 1429:                 daily arrival of new susceptables.
 1430:                 sa is rate of additional/removal of population by birth etc
 1431:             hh: float, np.array (M,)
 1432:                 fraction hospitalised from Is
 1433:             cc: float, np.array (M,)
 1434:                 fraction sent to intensive care from hospitalised.
 1435:             mm: float, np.array (M,)
 1436:                 mortality rate in intensive care
 1437:     M: int
 1438:         Number of compartments of individual for each class.
 1439:         I.e len(contactMatrix)
 1440:     Ni: np.array(9*M, )
 1441:         Initial number in each compartment and class
 1442: 
 1443:     Methods
 1444:     -------
 1445:     simulate
 1446:     """

 1689:     """
 1690:     Susceptible, Exposed, Activates, Infected, Removed (SEAIR)
 1691:     The infected class has 5 groups:
 1692:     * Ia: asymptomatic
 1693:     * Is: symptomatic
 1694:     * Ih: hospitalized
 1695:     * Ic: ICU
 1696:     * Im: Mortality
 1697: 
 1698:     S  ---> E
 1699:     E  ---> Ia, Is
 1700:     Ia ---> R
 1701:     Is ---> Ih, R
 1702:     Ih ---> Ic, R
 1703:     Ic ---> Im, R
 1704:     
 1705:     Latent inference class to be used when observed data is incomplete.
 1706:     
 1707:     Parameters
 1708:     ----------
 1709:     parameters: dict
 1710:         Contains the following keys:
 1711:             alpha: float
 1712:                 Estimate mean value of fraction of infected who are asymptomatic.
 1713:             beta: float
 1714:                 Estimate mean value of rate of spread of infection.
 1715:             gIa: float
 1716:                 Estimate mean value of rate of removal from asymptomatic individuals.
 1717:             gIs: float
 1718:                 Estimate mean value of rate of removal from symptomatic individuals.
 1719:             fsa: float
 1720:                 fraction by which symptomatic individuals self isolate.
 1721:             gE: float
 1722:                 Estimate mean value of rate of removal from exposeds individuals.
 1723:             gA: float
 1724:                 Estimate mean value of rate of removal from activated individuals.
 1725:             gIh: float
 1726:                 Rate of hospitalisation of infected individuals.
 1727:             gIc: float
 1728:                 Rate hospitalised individuals are moved to intensive care.
 1729:             cov: np.array
 1730:                 covariance matrix for all the estimated parameters.
 1731:             sa: float, np.array (M,)
 1732:                 daily arrival of new susceptables.
 1733:                 sa is rate of additional/removal of population by birth etc
 1734:             hh: float, np.array (M,)
 1735:                 fraction hospitalised from Is
 1736:             cc: float, np.array (M,)
 1737:                 fraction sent to intensive care from hospitalised.
 1738:             mm: float, np.array (M,)
 1739:                 mortality rate in intensive care
 1740:     M: int
 1741:         Number of compartments of individual for each class.
 1742:         I.e len(contactMatrix)
 1743:     Ni: np.array(9*M, )
 1744:         Initial number in each compartment and class
 1745: 
 1746:     Methods
 1747:     -------
 1748:     simulate
 1749:     """
 1750:     cdef:
+1751:         readonly int N, M,
